The animals escaped from the park on Monday. JOHANNESBURG - The Mpumalanga Tourism and Parks Agency says five lions that escaped from the Kruger National Park have attacked some cattle in the Komatipoort area.The agency says its officials are searching for the animals.Residents have been urged to be vigilant along the N4 in the Mananga area.The animals escaped from the park on Monday.Spokesperson Kholofelo Nkambule: &quot;The weather hasn't been good so we're waiting for the mist to clear so that they're able to use the helicopter to try and locate the lions. But at this moment, the guys are still at the scene trying to get these lions. There hasn't been any progress as yet.&quot;